THOUGHT: Now let me add a better fix that checks for select instructions in the loop.

```bash
sed -i '7361i\  // Also return true if the loop contains any select instructions, as these can
  // cause legitimate differences between cost models when used with reductions.
  if (any_of(TheLoop->blocks(), [](BasicBlock *BB) {
        return any_of(*BB, [](Instruction &I) { return isa<SelectInst>(&I); });
      }))
    return true;' /llvm-autofix-deps/llvm/llvm/llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/LoopVectorize.cpp
```

